<title>Auxiliary verbs</title>
<bgcolour>FFFFFF</bgcolour>
<darkcolour>3300cc</darkcolour><section><title>Auxiliary verbs</title><sectiontitle>Use auxiliary verbs &lt;I&gt;do, be&lt;/I&gt; and &lt;I&gt;have&lt;/I&gt; to make questions, short answers and negatives, and to form tenses.</sectiontitle><titlesound>Interm_gram_1_1_1.mp3</titlesound><text1>I have breakfast at seven o'clock.</text1><sound1>Interm_gram_1_1_2.mp3</sound1><text1a>When &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;do&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; you have breakfast?</text1a><text2></text2><sound2>Interm_gram_1_1_3.mp3</sound2><text2a>&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;Is&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;  he studying Italian?  Yes, he &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;is&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;.</text2a><titlesound2>Interm_gram_1_1_4.mp3</titlesound2><sectiontitle2>With the 'simple' tenses, use the verb &lt;I&gt;do&lt;/I&gt; as the auxiliary verb, except if the main verb is &lt;I&gt;be&lt;/I&gt;. </sectiontitle2><text3>main verb = smoke</text3><sound3>Interm_gram_1_1_5.mp3</sound3><text3a>&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;Does&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; he smoke? Yes, he &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;does&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;.</text3a><text4>main verb = be</text4><sound4>Interm_gram_1_1_6.mp3</sound4><text4a>&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;Are&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; you hungry?  No, I'm not.</text4a></section><section><title>Auxiliary verbs - making questions</title><sectiontitle>&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;'Yes' and 'No'&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; questions use &lt;I&gt;do/does&lt;/I&gt; in the present, &lt;I&gt;did&lt;/I&gt; in the past and &lt;I&gt;have/has&lt;/I&gt; in the Present Perfect. The order is ASV: auxiliary + subject + verb.</sectiontitle><titlesound>Interm_gram_1_1_7.mp3</titlesound><text1>(auxiliary + subject + verb)</text1><sound1>Interm_gram_1_1_8.mp3</sound1><text1a>&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;Did&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;               he         go      to work this morning? </text1a><text2>(auxiliary + subject + verb)</text2><sound2>Interm_gram_1_1_9.mp3</sound2><text2a>&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;Has&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;             he          finished breakfast?  </text2a><titlesound2>Interm_gram_1_1_10.mp3</titlesound2><sectiontitle2>In &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;Wh- questions&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; the question word comes before the auxiliary. The order is QASV: question word + auxiliary + subject + verb.</sectiontitle2><text3>(question word + auxiliary + subject + verb)</text3><sound3>Interm_gram_1_1_11.mp3</sound3><text3a>What time           &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;did&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;                he         get up?  </text3a><text4>(question word + auxiliary + subject + verb)</text4><sound4>Interm_gram_1_1_12.mp3</sound4><text4a>Where                &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;have&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;            they        gone?</text4a></section><section><title>Auxiliary verbs - short answers and negatives</title><sectiontitle>For short answers use the auxiliary verb from the question.</sectiontitle><titlesound>Interm_gram_1_1_13.mp3</titlesound><text1>&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;Has&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; she finished?</text1><sound1>Interm_gram_1_1_14.mp3</sound1><text1a>Yes, she &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;has.&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;</text1a><text2>&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;Do&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; you run regularly?</text2><sound2>Interm_gram_1_1_15.mp3</sound2><text2a>Yes, I &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;do.&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;</text2a><titlesound2>Interm_gram_1_1_16.mp3</titlesound2><sectiontitle2>For negatives use &lt;I&gt;don't/doesn't&lt;/I&gt; in the present, &lt;I&gt;didn't&lt;/I&gt; in the past and &lt;I&gt;haven't/hasn't&lt;/I&gt; in the Present Perfect.  </sectiontitle2><text3>I run very fast.</text3><sound3>Interm_gram_1_1_17.mp3</sound3><text3a>I &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;don't&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; run very fast.</text3a><text4>I &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;have&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; been here before.</text4><sound4>Interm_gram_1_1_18.mp3</sound4><text4a>I &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;haven't&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; been here before.</text4a></section></grammar>